======================================================================
Installation
======================================================================

To build the Xcode plug-in, first review and update the settings in
the Xcode/Slice2ObjcPlugin/config/Make.rules file. Next, execute the
following commands:

$ cd Xcode/Slice2ObjcPlugin
$ make

To install the plug-in:

$ make install

The Xcode plug-in is installed at the following location:

~/Library/Application Support/Developer/4.2/Xcode/Plug-ins/slice2objcplugin.pbplugin

If you have set XCODE_PLUGIN_ALL_USER=YES in Xcode/Slice2ObjcPlugin/config/Make.rules,
the plug-in will be installed for all users at the following location:

/Library/Application Support/Developer/4.2/Xcode/Plug-ins/slice2objcplugin.pbplugin

Note that admin access is required when installing the plug-in for all
users. You can prefix the "make install" command with sudo as shown
below:

$ sudo make install

